Borussia Dortmund right-back, Achraf Hakimi, has agreed to sign a five-year contract with Inter Milan. This was made known by respected transfer expert and sports journalist, Fabrizio Romano. Romano disclosed this in a tweet via his official Twitter account on Friday. According to him, the agreement to sign Hakimi, who is currently on loan at Dortmund from Real Madrid, is going to be finalized soon between Inter and the Los Blancos for €40million. “Inter are in advanced talks to sign Achraf Hakimi. He wants to leave Real Madrid to be a starter – Inter have contacted Real, and the player has accepted to listen to their bid. He’s the first target as a right-back for Antonio Conte. “Achraf Hakimi is really, really close to Inter. The agreement is going to be finalized soon between Inter and Real Madrid for €40M + add ons. Hakimi has already accepted to sign a five-year contract with Inter,” Romano tweeted. <img class="alignnone size-full wp-image-809858" src="https://dailypost.ng/wp-content/uploads/2020/06/romano.jpg" alt="" width="607" height="300" srcset="https://dailypost.ng/wp-content/uploads/2020/06/romano.jpg 607w, https://dailypost.ng/wp-content/uploads/2020/06/romano-300x148.jpg 300w" sizes="(max-width: 607px) 100vw, 607px">